# Anti-Patterns (DO NOT DO)

## Frontend

❌ Direct Supabase calls in NEW code (use C# API + feature flag)
❌ `any` type without justification
❌ Skipping realtime cleanup in useEffect return
❌ Prop drilling beyond 2 levels

## Backend

❌ Controllers without `[Authorize]`
❌ Returning 500 for downstream errors (use 502)
❌ Catching exceptions without logging
❌ Using service role key without admin role verification
❌ Application layer importing from Infrastructure

## General

❌ Committing secrets/API keys
❌ Skipping tests
❌ Committing without running linters
❌ Force-pushing to shared branches
